In later versions of Windows, it's difficult to reliably connect to a Confluence-hosted WebDAV share, because Windows (by default) won't handle basic authentication over a WebDAV share.

It would be helpful for customers to select which authentication system they could use for WebDAV access. Kerberos would be an ideal candidate, as users can map network drives with their existing Windows credentials (assuming of course that Confluence is set up to use the same credentials).
